text: Jeffrey "Jeff" Dunne (14 May 1956 â€“ 14 September 2020) was an Australian rules footballer. He played 102 games for St Kilda and Richmond in the top tier Victorian Football League during the 1970s and 1980s. He played for St Kilda from 1977 to 1983. He went on to coach East Launceston and North Launceston in the Tasmanian Football league in the mid 1980s. Dunne died of a heart attack on 14 September 2020, aged 64. ==References== ==Other websites== * Bio at Saints Hall of Fame Category:1956 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Deaths from myocardial infarction Category:Australian rules footballers Category:Sportspeople from Victoria (Australia)
